column5: Short Name

column9: Title

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a): Designate a qualified individual responsible for overseeing, implementing and enforcing your information security program
column7: Designate a qualified individual responsible for overseeing and implementing your information security program and enforcing your information security program (for purposes of this part, “Qualified Individual”). The Qualified Individual may be employed by you, an affiliate, or a service provider.
column9: Designate a qualified individual responsible for overseeing, implementing and enforcing your information security program

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (1): Retain responsibility for compliance with designating a qualified individual responsible for overseeing, implementing and enforcing your information security program
column7: To the extent the requirement in this paragraph (a) is met using a service provider or an affiliate, you shall retain responsibility for compliance with this part.
column9: Retain responsibility for compliance with designating a qualified individual responsible for overseeing, implementing and enforcing your information security program

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (2): Designate a senior member of your personnel responsible for direction and oversight of the Qualified Individual
column7: To the extent the requirement in this paragraph (a) is met using a service provider or an affiliate, you shall designate a senior member of your personnel responsible for direction and oversight of the Qualified Individual.
column9: Designate a senior member of your personnel responsible for direction and oversight of the Qualified Individual

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (3)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (a) (3): Require the service provider or affiliate to maintain an information security program that protects you in accordinace with the requirements
column7: To the extent the requirement in this paragraph (a) is met using a service provider or an affiliate, you shall require the service provider or affiliate to maintain an information security program that protects you in accordance with the requirements of this part.
column9: Require the service provider or affiliate to maintain an information security program that protects you in accordinace with the requirements

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b): Base your information security program on a risk assessment
column7: Base your information security program on a risk assessment that identifies reasonably foreseeable internal and external risks to the security, confidentiality, and integrity of customer information that could result in the unauthorized disclosure, misuse, alteration, destruction, or other compromise of such information, and assesses the sufficiency of any safeguards in place to control these risks.
column9: Base your information security program on a risk assessment

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (i)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (i): The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the evaluation and categorization of identified security risks or threats you face
column7: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the evaluation and categorization of identified security risks or threats you face.
column9: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the evaluation and categorization of identified security risks or threats you face

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (ii)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (ii): The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the assessment of the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of your information systems and customer information
column7: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the assessment of the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of your information systems and customer information, including the adequacy of the existing controls in the context of the identified risks or threats you face.
column9: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include criteria for the assessment of the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of your information systems and customer information

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (iii)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (1) (iii): The risk assessment shall be written and shall include requirements describing how identified risks will be mitigated or accepted based on the risk assessment
column7: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include requirements describing how identified risks will be mitigated or accepted based on the risk assessment and how the information security program will address the risks.
column9: The risk assessment shall be written and shall include requirements describing how identified risks will be mitigated or accepted based on the risk assessment

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (b) (2): You shall periodically perform additional risk assessments
column7: You shall periodically perform additional risk assessments that reexamine the reasonably foreseeable internal and external risks to the security, confidentiality, and integrity of customer information that could result in the unauthorized disclosure, misuse, alteration, destruction, or other compromise of such information, and reassess the sufficiency of any safeguards in place to control these risks.
column9: You shall periodically perform additional risk assessments

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (1) (i)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (1) (i): Implement and periodically review acess controls to authenticate and permit access only to authorized users
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including by implementing and periodically reviewing access controls, including technical and, as appropriate, physical controls to authenticate and permit access only to authorized users to protect against the unauthorized acquisition of customer information.
column9: Implement and periodically review acess controls to authenticate and permit access only to authorized users

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (1) (ii)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (1) (ii): Implement and periodically review access controls to limit authorized users' access only to customer information based on need
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including by implementing and periodically reviewing access controls, including technical and, as appropriate, physical controls to limit authorized users' access only to customer information that they need to perform their duties and functions, or, in the case of customers, to access their own information.
column9: Implement and periodically review access controls to limit authorized users' access only to customer information based on need

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (2): Identify and manage the data, personnel, devices, systems and facilities that enable you to achieve business purposes
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including by identifying and managing the data, personnel, devices, systems, and facilities that enable you to achieve business purposes in accordance with their relative importance to business objectives and your risk strategy.
column9: Identify and manage the data, personnel, devices, systems and facilities that enable you to achieve business purposes

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (3)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (3): Protect customer information with encryption
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including by protecting all customer information held or transmitted by you both in transit over external networks and at rest using encryption. To the extent you determine that encryption of customer information, either in transit over external networks or at rest, is infeasible, you may instead secure such customer information using effective alternative compensating controls reviewed and approved by your Qualified Individual.
column9: Protect customer information with encryption

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (4)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (4): Adopt secure development practices for in-house developed applications
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including adopting secure development practices for in-house developed applications utilized by you for transmitting, accessing, or storing customer information and procedures for evaluating, assessing, or testing the security of externally developed applications you utilize to transmit, access, or store customer information.
column9: Adopt secure development practices for in-house developed applications

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (5)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (5): Implement multi-factor authentication
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including implementing multi-factor authentication for any individual accessing any information system, unless your Qualified Individual has approved in writing the use of reasonably equivalent or more secure access controls.
column9: Implement multi-factor authentication

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (6) (i)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (6) (i): Develop, implement and maintain procedures for the secure disposal of customer information
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including developing, implementing, and maintaining procedures for the secure disposal of customer information in any format no later than two years after the last date the information is used in connection with the provision of a product or service to the customer to which it relates, unless such information is necessary for business operations or for other legitimate business purposes, is otherwise required to be retained by law or regulation, or where targeted disposal is not reasonably feasible due to the manner in which the information is maintained.
column9: Develop, implement and maintain procedures for the secure disposal of customer information

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (6) (Ii)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (6) (Ii): Periodically review your data retention policy
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including periodically reviewing your data retention policy to minimize the unnecessary retention of data.
column9: Periodically review your data retention policy

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (7)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (7): Adopt procedures for change management
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including adopting procedures for change management.
column9: Adopt procedures for change management

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (8)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (c) (8): Implement policies, procedures, and controls designed to monitor and log the activity of authorized users and detect unauthorized access
column7: Design and implement safeguards to control the risks you identity through risk assessment, including implementing policies, procedures, and controls designed to monitor and log the activity of authorized users and detect unauthorized access or use of, or tampering with, customer information by such users.
column9: Implement policies, procedures, and controls designed to monitor and log the activity of authorized users and detect unauthorized access

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (1): Monitor the effectiveness of key controls, systems and procedures
column7: Regularly test or otherwise monitor the effectiveness of the safeguards' key controls, systems, and procedures, including those to detect actual and attempted attacks on, or intrusions into, information systems.
column9: Monitor the effectiveness of key controls, systems and procedures

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2): Perform continuous monitoring or periodic penetration testing and vulnerability assessments
column7: For information systems, the monitoring and testing shall include continuous monitoring or periodic penetration testing and vulnerability assessments.
column9: Perform continuous monitoring or periodic penetration testing and vulnerability assessments

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2) (i)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2) (i): Conduct annual penetration testing of your information systems
column7: Absent effective continuous monitoring or other systems to detect, on an ongoing basis, changes in information systems that may create vulnerabilities, you shall conduct annual penetration testing of your information systems determined each given year based on relevant identified risks in accordance with the risk assessment.
column9: Conduct annual penetration testing of your information systems

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2) (ii)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (d) (2) (ii): Conduct vulnerability assessments at least every six months and whenever there are material changes to your operations or business arrangements
column7: Absent effective continuous monitoring or other systems to detect, on an ongoing basis, changes in information systems that may create vulnerabilities, you shall conduct vulnerability assessments, including any systemic scans or reviews of information systems reasonably designed to identify publicly known security vulnerabilities in your information systems based on the risk assessment, at least every six months; and whenever there are material changes to your operations or business arrangements; and whenever there are circumstances you know or have reason to know may have a material impact on your information security program.
column9: Conduct vulnerability assessments at least every six months and whenever there are material changes to your operations or business arrangements

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (1): Provide personnel with security awareness training
column7: Implement policies and procedures to ensure that personnel are able to enact your information security program by providing your personnel with security awareness training that is updated as necessary to reflect risks identified by the risk assessment.
column9: Provide personnel with security awareness training

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (2): Manage your information security risks and perform or oversee the information security program
column7: Implement policies and procedures to ensure that personnel are able to enact your information security program by utilizing qualified information security personnel employed by you or an affiliate or service provider sufficient to manage your information security risks and to perform or oversee the information security program.
column9: Manage your information security risks and perform or oversee the information security program

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (3)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (3): Information security personnel are provided with security updates and training
column7: Implement policies and procedures to ensure that personnel are able to enact your information security program by providing information security personnel with security updates and training sufficient to address relevant security risks.
column9: Information security personnel are provided with security updates and training

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (4)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (e) (4): Key information security personnel maintain current knowledge of changing information security threats and countermeasures
column7: Implement policies and procedures to ensure that personnel are able to enact your information security program by verifying that key information security personnel take steps to maintain current knowledge of changing information security threats and countermeasures.
column9: Key information security personnel maintain current knowledge of changing information security threats and countermeasures

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (1): Select and retain service providers that are capable of maintaing approprate safeguards
column7: Oversee service providers, by taking reasonable steps to select and retain service providers that are capable of maintaining appropriate safeguards for the customer information at issue.
column9: Select and retain service providers that are capable of maintaing approprate safeguards

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (2): Contractually require service providers to implement and maintain safeguards
column7: Oversee service providers, by requiring your service providers by contract to implement and maintain such safeguards.
column9: Contractually require service providers to implement and maintain safeguards

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (3)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (f) (3): Periodically assess service providers based on the risk they present and continued adequacy of their safeguards
column7: Oversee service providers, by periodically assessing your service providers based on the risk they present and the continued adequacy of their safeguards.
column9: Periodically assess service providers based on the risk they present and continued adequacy of their safeguards

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (g)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (g): Evaluate and adjust your information security program based on changing circumstances with material impact
column7: Evaluate and adjust your information security program in light of the results of the testing and monitoring required by paragraph (d) of this section; any material changes to your operations or business arrangements; the results of risk assessments performed under paragraph (b)(2) of this section; or any other circumstances that you know or have reason to know may have a material impact on your information security program.
column9: Evaluate and adjust your information security program based on changing circumstances with material impact

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h): Establish a written incident response plan
column7: Establish a written incident response plan designed to promptly respond to, and recover from, any security event materially affecting the confidentiality, integrity, or availability of customer information in your control.
column9: Establish a written incident response plan

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (1): Incident response plan shall address goals
column7: Such incident response plan shall address the goals of the incident response plan.
column9: Incident response plan shall address goals

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (2): Incident response plan shall address internal processes for responding to a security event
column7: Such incident response plan shall address the internal processes for responding to a security event.
column9: Incident response plan shall address internal processes for responding to a security event

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (3)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (3): Incident response plan shall address the definition of clear roles, responsibilities and levels of decision-making authority
column7: Such incident response plan shall address the definition of clear roles, responsibilities, and levels of decision-making authority.
column9: Incident response plan shall address the definition of clear roles, responsibilities and levels of decision-making authority

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (4)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (4): Incident response plan shall address external and internal communications and information sharing
column7: Such incident response plan shall address external and internal communications and information sharing.
column9: Incident response plan shall address external and internal communications and information sharing

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (5)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (5): Incident response plan shall address identification of requirements for the remediation of any identified weaknesses in information systems and associated controls
column7: Such incident response plan shall address identification of requirements for the remediation of any identified weaknesses in information systems and associated controls.
column9: Incident response plan shall address identification of requirements for the remediation of any identified weaknesses in information systems and associated controls

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (6)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (6): Incident response plan shall address documentation and reporting regarding security events and related incident response activities
column7: Such incident response plan shall address documentation and reporting regarding security events and related incident response activities.
column9: Incident response plan shall address documentation and reporting regarding security events and related incident response activities

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (7)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (h) (7): Incident response plan shall address the evaluation and revision of the incident response plan following a security event
column7: Such incident response plan shall address the evaluation and revision as necessary of the incident response plan following a security event.
column9: Incident response plan shall address the evaluation and revision of the incident response plan following a security event

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i): Qualified Individuals are required to report in writing, at least annually, to your board of directors or equivalent governing body
column7: Require your Qualified Individual to report in writing, regularly and at least annually, to your board of directors or equivalent governing body. If no such board of directors or equivalent governing body exists, such report shall be timely presented to a senior officer responsible for your information security program.
column9: Qualified Individuals are required to report in writing, at least annually, to your board of directors or equivalent governing body

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i) (1)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i) (1): Report to board shall include overall status of the information security program and compliance
column7: The report shall include the overall status of the information security program and your compliance with this part.
column9: Report to board shall include overall status of the information security program and compliance

column1: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information
column5: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i) (2)
column6: GLBA Standards for Safeguarding Customer Information § 314.4 (i) (2): Report to board shall include material matters related to the information security program
column7: The report shall include material matters related to the information security program, addressing issues such as risk assessment, risk management and control decisions, service provider arrangements, results of testing, security events or violations and management's responses thereto, and recommendations for changes in the information security program.
column9: Report to board shall include material matters related to the information security program
